---
description: Never use type assertions like `as`, or any other type shortcut, e.g. `any`, `!`, `Record<string, unknown>`, `{ [key: string]: unknown }`, `Object.*`, or `Reflect.*`
globs: '**/*.{ts,tsx,mts}'
alwaysApply: true
---

Never use type assertions like `as`, or any other type shortcut, e.g. `any`, `!`, `Record<string, unknown>`, `{ [key: string]: unknown }`, `Object.*`, or `Reflect.*` - they ALL disable the type system. The goal is to preserve type information as much as possible, not to work around this rule.

Instead, use type guards to narrow types to known, specific types derived from appropriate data structures or imports. DO NOT add type guards for 'Object' or any other type-guard that is a more complex way of saying `any` or `unknown` or `Record<string, unknown>`.
